Your problem mainly is your javascript looks for elements by id, so what it gets is the first element on DOM with that Id. Indeed, is working and is operating over the first elements with those Ids. 

It is not a good pattern to repeat ids on document elements. Even that, you should be looking for the sibling elements onblur instead of those with a fixed id. 

Maybe will be a better code using `querySelector` with some css selector by class name, like adding a class on those elements, so you can use it to style over all the elements on that document too or if you keep it like this use an attribute selector 

