Basically this works fine, but if the sender enters whitespaces, like &quot;Your new product&quot;, of course those appear in the encoded string as well, which isn&#39;t allowed. Also SpamAssassin gives a corresponding hint, which doesn&#39;t show up after removing the whitespaces in the subject input field of the form.

